<body>
    <div class="recipe">
        <h1>Handvo Recipe</h1>
        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup rice</li>
            <li>1/4 cup toor dal (pigeon peas)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup chana dal (split chickpeas)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup urad dal (split black gram)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup moong dal (split green gram)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup curd (yogurt)</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ginger paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon green chili paste</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons oil</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon mustard seeds</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon asafoetida (hing)</li>
            <li>A pinch of baking soda</li>
            <li>Curry leaves</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Wash the rice and dals together and soak them in water for around 4-5 hours.</li>
            <li>Drain the soaked rice and dals and grind them to a smooth batter using minimal water.</li>
            <li>Add curd, turmeric powder, red chili powder, ginger paste, green chili paste, and salt to the batter. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Cover the batter and let it ferment for about 6-8 hours or overnight.</li>
            <li>In a separate pan, heat oil and add mustard seeds, cumin seeds, asafoetida, and curry leaves. Let them splutter.</li>
            <li>Add the tempering to the fermented batter and mix well.</li>
            <li>Add baking soda and mix until the batter is light and frothy.</li>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) or use a stovetop pot for cooking.</li>
            <li>Pour the batter into a greased pan and bake in the preheated oven for 30-40 minutes, or cook on the stovetop until the handvo is cooked through and golden brown on top.</li>
            <li>Allow the handvo to cool down before slicing and serving.</li>
            <li>Your delicious and nutritious Handvo is ready to be enjoyed as a wholesome snack or meal!</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Handvo is a savory Gujarati dish made from mixed lentils and rice, often baked or cooked on the stovetop.</p>
    </div>
